The course provides an overview of themain terminology, principles and meaning of pre-school education; deals with the history of establishing kindergartens in Estonia and Europe; teaches child-centeredness in planning, conducting and analysing educational activities. Theory is supported by examples, practical tasks and advice. In seminars examples of students' practice acitivites are analysed, in practical classes students carry out relevant tasks. Action plans and lesson plans for conducting educational activities in kindergartens are compiled as independent work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  General aim is to form the theoretical basis necessary for subject specific studies in order to prepare students to plan and analyse educational activities in pre-schools.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student having completed the subject:
1. knows the main principles and history of pre-school education;
2. knows the basis and principles of planning, conducting, evaluating educational activities in kindergartens;
3. can compile a plan of educational activities based on child-centered approach.
